A 35-year-old bricklayer,  Archinong Koko, has been arrested for allegedly defiling a 5 year-old girl in Lagos. It was learnt that the incident occurred at Dansa Street, Anule Oshun. It was gathered that the suspect allegedly cornered the victim and took her to his room where he had canal knowledge of the toddler. Lagos state commissioner of Police, Imohimi Edgal, while parading the suspect on Monday, said on June 24, 2018 at about 17:40 hours, information was received by the Divisional Police Officer (DPO) Onireke Division that a 5-year-old girl has been defiled at Dansa, Abule-Oshun. A team of detectives were mobilized to the area where the suspect Achibong Koko ‘m’ age 35 years was arrested. The suspect, however, denied the allegation, saying “I am a bricklayer. I know the girl and her parents but I did not rape her. She did not come to my room. I am innocent of the allegations level against me.” The case has been transferred to the Gender section for further investigation and prosecution.